data.title: GnomeWorldWide
data.text:
The data provided by this page is regularly uploaded to GNOME's Orbital Laser Platform. The target visualisation display is updated irregularly for the time being. You can find an alternative target visualisation of the GNOME community at Google Maps.

Find Your Latitude & Longitude

With thanks to the authors of the Debian Developer Locations Map!

Coordinates of places all around the world, with exact maps for USA, Canada and most of Europe: http://www.multimap.com/

Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names: http://www.getty.edu/research/conducting_research/vocabularies/tgn/

Good starting point: http://www.ckdhr.com/dns-loc/finding.html

GPS locations for airports: http://www.airnav.com/

Google Maps-based lat-long finder: http://www.satsig.net/maps/lat-long-finder.htm

Australian database: http://www.ga.gov.au/map/names/

Canadian database: http://GeoNa/krishmes.NRCan.gc.ca/

Get your coordinates and horoscope too: http://www.astro.com/cgi/aq.cgi?lang=e

another site which shows coordinates bottom left: http://www.maporama.com/share/

Find coordinates of place names in New Zealand: http://www.linz.govt.nz/placenames/find-names/topographic-names-db/index.aspx

Find Irish place names in Placenames Database of Ireland also Translate into Irish or English : http://www.logainm.ie/
